I researched how infinity dodecahedrons work and what materials are needed. The idea is to create a 12-sided polyhedron with each face being a two-way mirror and LED strips on every edge which creates an infinite lighting tunnel in every direction.

I figured out that two-way mirror sheets in the size I want them are VERY expensive, but the same effect can be achieved using clear, normal acrylic sheets and 1-way mirror film. This reduces the cost but allows for the same effect.

I found an online guide that will help me understand the geometry, LED  routing, and how to power it. The guide also confirmed that the project will fit within the budget.

